documentation.text: @dev Returns the length of the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
@dev Returns the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.

@dev Add an address to the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
 - Sets whitelist flag to true (preventing duplicate records).
 - Pushes address to the whitelist.
 - Stores the index of the recently added record. (lookup support).
 Requirements:
 - The contract must be called by the owner.
 - The contract must not have (reentrant) calls.
 - The contract must not have the input address stored in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
@dev Returns the index of the input address from the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
@dev Returns true if the input address is found in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array, and false otherwise.

@dev Update an existing address to another one in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
 - Sets whitelist flag of the '_addressTo' to true (preventing duplicate records).
 - Updates an address to another one in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
 - Swaps the index of the '_addressTo' record with the 'oldAccountIndex'.
 - Resets the index of the 'oldAccountIndex' back to its default value. (0)
 - Resets the flag of the 'oldAccountIndex' back to its default value. (false)
 Requirements:
 - The contract must be called by the owner.
 - The contract must not have (reentrant) calls.
 - The 'whitelistedAccounts' array must have at least one record.
 - The contract must not have the '_addressTo' update stored in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
 - The 'whitelistedAccounts' array must contain the '_addressFrom' address.

@dev Delete an existing address from the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
 - Swaps the '_addressToDelete' element with the last element of the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
 - Swaps the index of the 'addressToDeleteIndex' record with the 'lastItemAddress'.
 - Resets the index of the '_addressToDelete' back to its default value. (0)
 - Resets the flag of the '_addressToDelete' back to its default value. (false)
 Requirements:
 - The contract must be called by the owner.
 - The contract must not have (reentrant) calls.
 - The 'whitelistedAccounts' array must have at least one record.
 - The 'whitelistedAccounts' array must contain the '_addressToDelete' address.

devdoc.details: Contract that allows the contract owner to create, read, update & delete records from a whitelist.

deleteFromWhitelist(address).details: Delete an existing address from the 'whitelistedAccounts' array. - Swaps the '_addressToDelete' element with the last element of the 'whitelistedAccounts' array. - Swaps the index of the 'addressToDeleteIndex' record with the 'lastItemAddress'. - Resets the index of the '_addressToDelete' back to its default value. (0) - Resets the flag of the '_addressToDelete' back to its default value. (false) Requirements: - The contract must be called by the owner. - The contract must not have (reentrant) calls. - The 'whitelistedAccounts' array must have at least one record. - The 'whitelistedAccounts' array must contain the '_addressToDelete' address.

getWhitelistLength().details: Returns the length of the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

returnAccountIndex(address).details: Returns the index of the input address from the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateWhitelist(address,address).details: Update an existing address to another one in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array. - Sets whitelist flag of the '_addressTo' to true (preventing duplicate records). - Updates an address to another one in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array. - Swaps the index of the '_addressTo' record with the 'oldAccountIndex'. - Resets the index of the 'oldAccountIndex' back to its default value. (0) - Resets the flag of the 'oldAccountIndex' back to its default value. (false) Requirements: - The contract must be called by the owner. - The contract must not have (reentrant) calls. - The 'whitelistedAccounts' array must have at least one record. - The contract must not have the '_addressTo' update stored in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array. - The 'whitelistedAccounts' array must contain the '_addressFrom' address.

verifyCustomAddress(address).details: Returns true if the input address is found in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array, and false otherwise.

whiteListAddress(address).details: Add an address to the 'whitelistedAccounts' array. - Sets whitelist flag to true (preventing duplicate records). - Pushes address to the whitelist. - Stores the index of the recently added record. (lookup support). Requirements: - The contract must be called by the owner. - The contract must not have (reentrant) calls. - The contract must not have the input address stored in the 'whitelistedAccounts' array.
